quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"You who wraps himself [in his clothing]"
  73,2,"stay up during the night, except for a little"
  73,3,"for half of it, or a little less"
  73,4,"or a little more, and recite the Qur'an slowly and distinctly"
  73,5,We will send a weighty message to you
  73,6,Rising at night has a stronger effect and is more conducive to concentration
  73,7,"In the daytime, you are kept busy for long periods"
  73,8,So remember to call upon the name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him wholeheartedly
  73,9,"The Lord of the East and the West; there is no god but Him. So, assign to Him alone the power to determine your fate"
  73,10,"And patiently endure what they say, and withdraw from them politely"
  73,11,and leave those who deny the truth and live in luxury to Me. Just bear with them a little longer
  73,12,We have shackles and Hell
  73,13,And food that chokes and a painful punishment reserved for them
  73,14,"on the Day when the earth and the mountains tremble, and the mountains become heaps of sand"
  73,15,"We have sent to you a messenger, a witness over you just as We sent to Pharaoh a messenger"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a crushing grip"
  73,17,"How, then, if you refuse to acknowledge the truth, will you protect yourself from a Day which will turn the children gray-haired"
  73,18,A Day when the heavens will shatter. God's promise is always fulfilled
  73,19,"This is a reminder, so let anyone who wills set a path towards his Lord"